hw5

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • hw5.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    Graph is a mutable interface for representing a directed labeled multigraph. Graph is a collection of GraphNodes, each linked with GraphEdges reaching out of them. Mutable meaning the user can add or remove nodes and edges from the graph as they desire.

    A Graph can be described as {n_1 = [e_n_1_1, ... ,e_n_1_n], ... , n_m = [e_n_m_1, ... ,e_n_m_n]}, where n_1 ... n_m are the nodes in the graph and [e_n_1_1, ... ,e_n_1_n] are the edges reaching out from n_1 ... [e_n_m_1, ... ,e_n_m_n] are the edges reaching out from n_m

    An example of a Graph includes: {GraphNode("a") = [GraphEdge(GraphNode("a"), GraphNode("b"))], GraphNode("b") = [GraphEdge(GraphNode("b"), GraphNode("a"))]} and {GraphNode("a") = [GraphEdge(GraphNode("a"), GraphNode("b"))], GraphNode("b") = [GraphEdge(GraphNode("b"), GraphNode("c"))], GraphNode("c") = [GraphEdge(GraphNode("c"), GraphNode("a"))]}

    Author:
    Young Bin Cho
